How to fix the WordPress error: "Fatal error: Allowed memory size of 33554432 bytes exhausted"?

1. Create a .htaccess file at the root of public_html.

Include this after the Rewrite rules:

suPHP_ConfigPath /home/username/public_html/

Replace username with the name you used to login to the cPanel.

&nbsp;

2. Create a php.ini files at the root of public_html

memory_limit = 64M;

&nbsp;

3. In the wp-config.php include just before /* That's all, stop editing! Happy blogging. */:

define('WP_MEMORY_LIMIT', '64M');

&nbsp;

More details found here:

http://www.planetdomain.com/support/web-hosting/changing-memory-limit-for-php-using-php-ini

http://codex.wordpress.org/Editing_wp-config.php
